[00:00.45]	[CAESAR's house.,]
[00:01.36]	[Thunder and lightning. Enter CAESAR, in his
[00:04.99]	+ night-gown]
[00:06.28]CAESAR	Nor heaven nor earth have been at peace to-night:
[00:10.44]	Thrice hath Calpurnia in her sleep cried out,
[00:14.31]	'Help, ho! they murder Caesar!' Who's within?
[00:17.79]	[Enter a Servant]
[00:18.70]Servant	My lord?
[00:19.76]CAESAR	Go bid the priests do present sacrifice
[00:23.24]	And bring me their opinions of success.
[00:26.65]Servant	I will, my lord.
[00:28.24]	[Exit]
[00:29.15]	[Enter CALPURNIA]
[00:30.06]CALPURNIA	What mean you, Caesar? think you to walk forth?
[00:33.92]	You shall not stir out of your house to-day.
[00:37.70]CAESAR	Caesar shall forth: the things that threaten'd me
[00:41.87]	Ne'er look'd but on my back; when they shall see
[00:45.96]	The face of Caesar, they are vanished.
[00:49.21]CALPURNIA	Caesar, I never stood on ceremonies,
[00:52.32]	Yet now they fright me. There is one within,
[00:56.03]	Besides the things that we have heard and seen,
[01:00.04]	Recounts most horrid sights seen by the watch.
[01:03.98]	A lioness hath whelped in the streets;
[01:07.31]	And graves have yawn'd, and yielded up their dead;
[01:11.48]	Fierce fiery warriors fought upon the clouds,
[01:15.34]	In ranks and squadrons and right form of war,
