[01:25.94]	Horses did neigh, and dying men did groan,
[01:29.50]	And ghosts did shriek and squeal about the streets.
[01:33.81]	O Caesar! these things are beyond all use,
[01:37.37]	And I do fear them.
[01:39.27]CAESAR	What can be avoided
[01:41.23]	Whose end is purposed by the mighty gods?
[01:44.79]	Yet Caesar shall go forth; for these predictions
[01:48.88]	Are to the world in general as to Caesar.
[01:52.44]CALPURNIA	When beggars die, there are no comets seen;
